S10.about: The touching final season of this Emmy-winning sitcom wraps up the stories of the Manhattan sextet, including Ross and Rachel's on-and-off romance.

S10E1.title: The One After Joey and Rachel Kiss
S10E1.des: Ross has kissed Charlie although she is still officially dating Joey. Joey and Rachel have kissed as well, but they agonize over how to tell Ross.

S10E2.title: The One Where Ross Is Fine
S10E2.des: Rachel, Joey and Charlie attend an uncomfortable dinner party at Ross's apartment. Former surrogate mother Phoebe is visited by her brother, Frank Jr.

S10E3.title: The One with Ross's Tan
S10E3.des: Monica and Phoebe's annoying friend visits, causing a rift between the women. Ross goes to a tanning salon but fails to follow the directions.

S10E4.title: The One with the Cake
S10E4.des: When Ross dashes out to help Rachel for Emma's birthday party, he leaves Joey in charge of keeping everybody in the apartment until they return.

S10E5.title: The One Where Rachel's Sister Babysits
S10E5.des: Rachel thinks her annoying, self-indulgent younger sister, Amy, is finally on the verge of making a major change in her attitude.

S10E6.title: The One with Ross's Grant
S10E6.des: Ross has the chance to receive a grant, but must break up with Charlie to get it. Phoebe tries to give a hideous painting to Monica and Rachel.

S10E7.title: The One with The Home Study
S10E7.des: Phoebe and Mike opt to have a small wedding and donate the extra money to a children's charity -- only to demand it all back later.

S10E8.title: The One with the Late Thanksgiving
S10E8.des: Monica prepares a fabulous Thanksgiving feast for the gang, but she becomes furious when everyone arrives late to the gathering.

S10E9.title: The One with the Birth Mother
S10E9.des: Nervous and excited, Monica and Chandler travel to Ohio to meet a pregnant woman who is considering allowing them to adopt her child when it's born.

S10E10.title: The One Where Chandler Gets Caught
S10E10.des: When Phoebe and Rachel see Chandler getting into a car with a pretty woman during work hours, they follow him.

S10E11.title: The One Where the Stripper Cries
S10E11.des: Joey appears as a celebrity contestant on "The $100,000 Pyramid," but his dubious IQ puts his partner's prize money at risk.

S10E12.title: The One with Phoebe's Wedding
S10E12.des: Phoebe's wedding planner, Monica, is driving everyone around her crazy. Chandler and Ross lobby Rachel to choose one of them as a groomsman.

S10E13.title: The One Where Joey Speaks French
S10E13.des: Monica and Chandler show Erica, the mother of the unborn baby they want to adopt, the sights of New York. Joey implores Phoebe to teach him French.

S10E14.title: The One with Princess Consuela
S10E14.des: Rachel nearly gags on her meal when she goes on a job interview at a restaurant and sits next to her current boss. Phoebe considers changing her name.

S10E15.title: The One Where Estelle Dies
S10E15.des: When Rachel makes a startling announcement, Ross schemes to get her former job back for her. Joey is flustered by the upheaval in his friends' lives.

S10E16.title: The One with Rachel's Going Away Party
S10E16.des: As Rachel prepares to leave for Paris, the gang hosts a farewell party for her. But one friend is offended when he is excluded.

S10E17.title: The Last One: Part 1 & Part 2
S10E17.des: On their last day together, Rachel, Monica, Phoebe, Joey, Chandler and Ross reflect on their shared times with bittersweet emotion.

S1.about: Season 1 of the hit sitcom introduces us to hapless Ross, spoiled Rachel, quirky Chandler, dim-witted Joey, free-spirited Phoebe and uptight Monica.

S1E1.title: The One Where Monica Gets a Roommate (Pilot)
S1E1.des: Rachel runs from her wedding and meets the friends in the coffee place. Ross is depressed about his divorce but he still has a crush on Rachel.

S1E2.title: The One with the Sonogram at the End
S1E2.des: Ross's lesbian ex-wife is pregnant with his child, and he doesn't like her choice of a last name for the baby.

S1E3.title: The One with the Thumb
S1E3.des: A soda company gives Phoebe $7,000 after she finds a dismembered thumb in a can of soda.

S1E4.title: The One with George Stephanopoulos
S1E4.des: A deliveryman accidentally brings a pizza meant for George Stephanopoulos, who lives across the street from the girls.

S1E5.title: The One with the East German Laundry Detergent
S1E5.des: Ross helps Rachel do laundry and considers the evening a first date. Joey has Monica pose as his new girlfriend.

S1E6.title: The One with the Butt
S1E6.des: Joey gets his big film break when he's hired to be Al Pacino's stunt butt.

S1E7.title: The One with the Blackout
S1E7.des: During a citywide blackout, Ross tries to tell Rachel that he likes her.

S1E8.title: The One Where Nana Dies Twice
S1E8.des: Monica and Ross mourn the death of their grandmother. Chandler questions his sexuality.

S1E9.title: The One Where Underdog Gets Away
S1E9.des: Monica's first Thanksgiving dinner for the gang burns when they all run to the rooftop to see the runaway Underdog balloon from the parade.

S1E10.title: The One with the Monkey
S1E10.des: The gang makes and then breaks a pact to celebrate New Year's Eve without dates. Lonely Ross gets a roommate: a monkey named Marcel.

S1E11.title: The One with Mrs. Bing
S1E11.des: When Chandler's romance novelist mother comes to New York to visit him, Joey catches her and Ross kissing.

S1E12.title: The One with the Dozen Lasagnas
S1E12.des: Monica gives Paolo one of the dozen lasagnas she made for her aunt, who doesn't want them anymore because they've got meat in them.

S1E13.title: The One with the Boobies
S1E13.des: Chandler accidentally sees Rachel wandering around topless after her shower, so Rachel tries to even the score.

S1E14.title: The One with the Candy Hearts
S1E14.des: Joey fixes up Chandler and Janice, and Ross runs into Carol and Susan on a Valentine's Day date.

S1E15.title: The One with the Stoned Guy
S1E15.des: Monica cooks a gourmet meal for a restaurateur looking for a new chef, but unfortunately, he's stoned.

S1E16.title: The One with the Two Parts: Part 1
S1E16.des: Joey falls for Phoebe's twin sister, making Phoebe feel neglected. Ross attends Lamaze classes with Carol and Susan.

S1E17.title: The One with the Two Parts: Part 2
S1E17.des: When Rachel sprains her ankle and has no insurance, she talks Monica into trading identities so she can use Monica's coverage.

S1E18.title: The One with All the Poker
S1E18.des: Rachel interviews for a job as an assistant buyer at Saks Fifth Avenue. The women face the men in a not-so-friendly game of poker.

S1E19.title: The One Where the Monkey Gets Away
S1E19.des: The gang searches for Marcel, who slipped out of the apartment while Rachel was caring for him.

S1E20.title: The One with the Evil Orthodontist
S1E20.des: Rachel and Barry start dating again, even though he's engaged to Mindy, who wants Rachel to be her maid of honor.

S1E21.title: The One with the Fake Monica
S1E21.des: When Monica's credit card is stolen, she decides to catch the thief.

S1E22.title: The One with the Ick Factor
S1E22.des: After losing his virginity to her, Monica's boyfriend reveals that he's a high school senior. Phoebe temps as Chandler's secretary.

S1E23.title: The One with the Birth
S1E23.des: Carol goes into labor while Ross, Phoebe and Susan get locked in a closet.

S1E24.title: The One Where Rachel Finds Out
S1E24.des: During Rachel's birthday party, Chandler accidentally lets it slip that Ross is in love with her.

S8.about: Rachel is pregnant and faces single parenthood, while Joey agonizes over his feelings for her. Chandler and Monica are now dealing with married life.

S8E1.title: The One After I Do
S8E1.des: Monica and Chandler's wedding reception is almost upstaged by the news that Rachel is pregnant.

S8E2.title: The One with the Red Sweater
S8E2.des: As they prepare to leave the wedding hotel, an excited Monica and Phoebe speculate about who might be the father of pregnant Rachel's baby.

S8E3.title: The One Where Rachel Tells ...
S8E3.des: Everyone seems to know who the father of Rachel's unborn baby is except for the man himself: Ross.

S8E4.title: The One with the Videotape
S8E4.des: Ross and Rachel try to explain how they ended up in bed together six weeks earlier, but the conversation quickly devolves into an argument.

S8E5.title: The One with Rachel's Date
S8E5.des: Ross is horrified to learn that Rachel is going on a date with a handsome actor, especially since she is pregnant with Ross' child.

S8E6.title: The One with the Halloween Party
S8E6.des: At Monica's Halloween party, Phoebe becomes attracted to Eric, the friendly fiancé of her flighty twin, Ursula.

S8E7.title: The One with the Stain
S8E7.des: Ross is happy to learn that pregnant Rachel wants to find her own apartment. Phoebe is ecstatic that Eric has chosen her over her twin sister, Ursula.

S8E8.title: The One with the Stripper
S8E8.des: Rachel nervously tells her short-tempered father that she is pregnant with Ross' baby. Monica feels guilty for denying Chandler a bachelor party.

S8E9.title: The One with the Rumor
S8E9.des: Monica invites Will, her high school friend, over for Thanksgiving dinner -- unaware that he isn't too fond of Rachel.

S8E10.title: The One with Monica's Boots
S8E10.des: Chandler becomes upset when Monica spends a fortune on a luxurious pair of black boots. Phoebe tries to meet Sting.

S8E11.title: The One with the Creepy Holiday Card
S8E11.des: Ross becomes nervous when his new girlfriend, Mona, wants to mail cute Christmas cards with both of their pictures on it.

S8E12.title: The One Where Joey Dates Rachel
S8E12.des: In order to prepare Joey for his big date the following night, Rachel eagerly agrees to accompany him for an evening out.

S8E13.title: The One Where Chandler Takes a Bath
S8E13.des: As Joey agonizes over his secret affection for Rachel, Monica mistakenly thinks that he is infatuated with Phoebe.

S8E14.title: The One with the Secret Closet
S8E14.des: Joey realizes that his feelings for Rachel are excluding Ross from the joys of impending fatherhood. Chandler is obsessed with Monica's locked closet.

S8E15.title: The One with the Birthing Video
S8E15.des: Monica prepares a special Valentine's Day for Chandler, who is too shocked to respond favorably after accidentally viewing the wrong videotape.

S8E16.title: The One Where Joey Tells Rachel
S8E16.des: Guilt-ridden Joey confesses his love for Rachel to the flabbergasted Ross. Phoebe's new boyfriend shares numerous personality traits with Monica.

S8E17.title: The One with the Tea Leaves
S8E17.des: Feeling awkward after revealing his feelings to Rachel, Joey avoids contact with her. Phoebe believes she will soon meet the man of her dreams.

S8E18.title: The One in Massapequa
S8E18.des: Monica must give a toast at a 35th wedding anniversary party for her parents. Jack and Judy ask Ross and Rachel to pretend to be married at the party.

S8E19.title: The One with Joey's Interview
S8E19.des: Joey is thrilled when his name is used in a Soap Opera Digest crossword puzzle, yet he is reluctant to let the magazine do a profile about him.

S8E20.title: The One with the Baby Shower
S8E20.des: Rachel panics during a party in anticipation of her baby's birth when she realizes how unprepared she is to care for an infant.

S8E21.title: The One with the Cooking Class
S8E21.des: Monica tries to sway a food critic's opinion. Nervous about a major job interview, Chandler receives some questionable coaching from Phoebe.

S8E22.title: The One Where Rachel Is Late
S8E22.des: When Rachel's pregnancy goes beyond her projected delivery date, the pain makes Rachel increasingly irritable.

S8E23.title: The One Where Rachel Has a Baby: Part 1
S8E23.des: Rachel waits in the hospital maternity ward with Ross, as numerous other pregnant women are wheeled in while Rachel's painful labor continues.

S8E24.title: The One Where Rachel Has a Baby: Part 2
S8E24.des: Rachel gives birth to a beautiful girl, and Ross kisses Rachel. Both hiding their feelings, they wonder how to proceed.

S6.about: In Season 6 of the Emmy-winning series, Ross doesn't tell Rachel that their accidental marriage was never annulled, but he does tell Phoebe.

S6E1.title: The One After Vegas
S6E1.des: Ross and Rachel wake up together, not realizing they got married the night before. Monica and Chandler talk about moving in together.

S6E2.title: The One Where Ross Hugs Rachel
S6E2.des: Ross has to tell Rachel that they're still married. Chandler is moving in with Monica, and Rachel assumes that she'll be living with them.

S6E3.title: The One with Ross's Denial
S6E3.des: Ross asks Rachel to be his roommate, refusing to admit that he still has feelings for her. Monica and Chandler argue about the apartment.

S6E4.title: The One Where Joey Loses His Insurance
S6E4.des: Joey gets a hernia but doesn't have health insurance to cover getting it treated. Ross puts on a British accent while teaching his new class.

S6E5.title: The One with Joey's Porsche
S6E5.des: Joey pretends that he owns a Porsche. After the incident in Vegas, Ross is feeling like a failure because he's about to get his third divorce.

S6E6.title: The One on the Last Night
S6E6.des: Joey is broke but won't accept help from his friends, so Chandler lets him "win" money in a game. Rachel gets ready to move and fights with Monica.

S6E7.title: The One Where Phoebe Runs
S6E7.des: Phoebe looks goofy when she runs, so Rachel is embarrassed to go jogging with her. Joey is attracted to his new roommate, Janine.

S6E8.title: The One with Ross's Teeth
S6E8.des: Ross whitens his teeth to impress a girl, but he goes way overboard. Phoebe tells Rachel that she hooked up with Ralph Lauren.

S6E9.title: The One Where Ross Got High
S6E9.des: Monica and Ross's parents don't like Chandler because they think he smoked pot in college. Rachel makes a disgusting Thanksgiving dessert.

S6E10.title: The One with the Routine
S6E10.des: Joey, Ross and Monica dance on "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve." The rest of the gang searches for Monica's hidden Christmas presents.

S6E11.title: The One with the Apothecary Table
S6E11.des: Rachel buys a table from a fancy store and tells Phoebe she got it at the flea market. Janine tells Joey that she doesn't like Monica and Chandler.

S6E12.title: The One with the Joke
S6E12.des: Chandler and Ross both try to take credit for a joke. Monica is insulted when Phoebe says Rachel would make a better girlfriend than her.

S6E13.title: The One with Rachel's Sister
S6E13.des: Rachel's sister, Jill, comes to Rachel for help after her parents cut her off financially. Working as a waiter, Joey hits on the Central Perk customers.

S6E14.title: The One Where Chandler Can't Cry
S6E14.des: When Chandler says he hardly ever cries, everyone tries to make it happen. Rachel's sister, Jill, dates Ross to annoy Rachel.

S6E15.title: The One That Could Have Been: Part 1
S6E15.des: The gang imagines what life would've been like if Rachel had married Barry, Phoebe became a business executive and Monica was still fat.

S6E16.title: The One That Could Have Been: Part 2
S6E16.des: The friends continue to ponder an alternate past in which fat Monica seduces Chandler and married Rachel almost cheats on Barry with Joey.

S6E17.title: The One with Unagi
S6E17.des: When Rachel and Phoebe take a self-defense class, Ross claims he's a martial arts expert. Chandler and Monica forget to buy Valentine's Day gifts.

S6E18.title: The One Where Ross Dates a Student
S6E18.des: One of Ross's students asks him on a date. When there's a fire in their apartment, Rachel and Phoebe have to stay with Joey or Monica.

S6E19.title: The One with Joey's Fridge
S6E19.des: Joey tries to convince someone to buy him a new fridge. Ross is worried that his girlfriend will cheat on him during spring break.

S6E20.title: The One with Mac and C.H.E.E.S.E
S6E20.des: Joey's up for the lead in a new TV show, but Chandler forgets to leave him a message that the audition time has changed.

S6E21.title: The One Where Ross Meets Elizabeth's Dad
S6E21.des: Ross makes a bad impression on Elizabeth's dad, who doesn't approve of them dating. But Elizabeth's dad takes an interest in Rachel.

S6E22.title: The One Where Paul's the Man
S6E22.des: Ross and Elizabeth sneak off to the family cabin, where Rachel and Paul -- who threatened to have Ross fired for dating a student -- are also headed.

S6E23.title: The One with the Ring
S6E23.des: Phoebe is the only one who knows that Chandler is going to propose to Monica, and she lies to Ross to keep him from finding out.

S6E24.title: The One with the Proposal: Part 1
S6E24.des: Chandler's plan to propose to Monica is interrupted when they run into Richard. Joey accidentally buys a boat for $20,000 at a silent auction.

S6E25.title: The One with the Proposal: Part 2
S6E25.des: Richard tells Monica he still loves her. Chandler's attempt to make the proposal a surprise leaves Monica thinking he doesn't want to marry her.

S9.about: Rachel finds herself surprisingly adept at taking care of Emma but struggles to define her complicated relationships with Joey and Ross.

S9E1.title: The One Where No One Proposes
S9E1.des: Because of a misunderstanding, Rachel finds herself engaged to Joey instead of Ross, who was planning to propose.

S9E2.title: The One Where Emma Cries
S9E2.des: Somebody ends up in the hospital when Joey attempts to apologize to Ross for mistakenly asking Rachel to marry him.

S9E3.title: The One with the Pediatrician
S9E3.des: Rachel's constant calls to Emma's pediatrician force him to reject her as a patient.

S9E4.title: The One with the Sharks
S9E4.des: Phoebe fears losing Mike, and her self-doubt is exacerbated by Ross' foolish comments.

S9E5.title: The One with Phoebe's Birthday Dinner
S9E5.des: Rachel is afraid to leave Emma with a babysitter.

S9E6.title: The One with the Male Nanny
S9E6.des: Ross jealously mocks Rachel's choice of an oversensitive male nanny for Emma.

S9E7.title: The One with Ross' Inappropriate Song
S9E7.des: When Chandler's former romantic rival decides to sell his apartment, Chandler persuades Joey to help him inspect it on the sly.

S9E8.title: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
S9E8.des: Rachel's self-centered younger sister, Amy, ruins everyone's Thanksgiving dinner with her uncensored observations.

S9E9.title: The One with Rachel's Phone Number
S9E9.des: While on a night out with Phoebe, Rachel impulsively gives her telephone number to a handsome restaurant patron.

S9E10.title: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
S9E10.des: Because of a critical deadline at work, Chandler is stuck spending Christmas in Tulsa, Okla.

S9E11.title: The One Where Rachel Goes Back to Work
S9E11.des: While visiting her workplace to show off baby Emma, Rachel is surprised to find a handsome temp who's been doing her job.

S9E12.title: The One with Phoebe's Rats
S9E12.des: Rachel is irritated to learn that her handsome workplace rival has been invited to her birthday party.

S9E13.title: The One Where Monica Sings
S9E13.des: While Rachel sorts out her conflicted feelings for Gavin, Ross sets out to make her jealous, enlisting Chandler to help him meet attractive women.

S9E14.title: The One with the Blind Dates
S9E14.des: In an attempt to reunite Rachel and Ross, Joey and Phoebe arrange awful blind dates for both of them.

S9E15.title: The One with the Mugging
S9E15.des: Joey develops an unusual acting method to impress a famous fellow actor. Meanwhile, Chandler accepts an internship at an advertising agency.

S9E16.title: The One with the Boob Job
S9E16.des: Phoebe asks Mike to move in with her, but coming so close to married life may cause trouble in their relationship.

S9E17.title: The One with the Memorial Service
S9E17.des: When Chandler jokingly posts an outrageous biography about Ross on his college alumni Web site, Ross retaliates.

S9E18.title: The One with the Lottery
S9E18.des: Hoping to win a huge jackpot, the friends pool their money and buy dozens of lottery tickets.

S9E19.title: The One with Rachel's Dream
S9E19.des: Nervous because his daytime-drama role requires him to act as if he's deeply in love with a woman, Joey rehearses with Rachel.

S9E20.title: The One with the Soap Opera Party
S9E20.des: Ross is excited when he meets fellow paleontologist Charlie Wheeler, who's a stunning beauty.

S9E21.title: The One with the Fertility Test
S9E21.des: Ross is in agony because Charlie is dating Joey. Meanwhile, Chandler and Monica visit a fertility clinic.

S9E22.title: The One with the Donor
S9E22.des: Disappointed to learn that they can't conceive a baby naturally, Monica and Chandler consider their options.

S9E23.title: The One in Barbados
S9E23.des: The gang accompanies Ross to a paleontology convention in Barbados, where Ross bonds with Charlie while Joey and Rachel get drunk together.

S4.about: Chandler makes amends to Joey by spending Thanksgiving in a box, Monica finally lands her dream job of head chef, and Phoebe supports her brother.

S4E1.title: The One with the Jellyfish
S4E1.des: Ross dates Rachel again after unwittingly agreeing to take responsibility for their breakup. Monica is stung by a jellyfish.

S4E2.title: The One with the Cat
S4E2.des: Phoebe believes that the cat that jumped into her guitar case in Central Perk contains the spirit of her adoptive mom.

S4E3.title: The One with the 'Cuffs
S4E3.des: Monica tries to prove that she can cater a gourmet meal for her mother. Chandler gets into an embarrassing situation while dating Rachel's boss.

S4E4.title: The One with the Ballroom Dancing
S4E4.des: Joey teaches the building superintendent ballroom dancing to prevent him from evicting Rachel and Monica. Phoebe wants to date a massage client.

S4E5.title: The One with Joey's New Girlfriend
S4E5.des: Joey thinks that Chandler hates Joey's new girlfriend -- but the truth is that Chandler avoids her because he is so attracted to her.

S4E6.title: The One with the Dirty Girl
S4E6.des: Ross's beautiful new girlfriend has a very dirty apartment. Chandler becomes more familiar with Joey's girlfriend.

S4E7.title: The One Where Chandler Crosses the Line
S4E7.des: Chandler is guilt-ridden after kissing Joey's girlfriend. Ross's musical talents are not as amazing as he and Phoebe think.

S4E8.title: The One with Chandler in a Box
S4E8.des: On Thanksgiving, Joey punishes Chandler for kissing Kathy. Monica gets a surprise when she visits an eye doctor: He's her former boyfriend's son.

S4E9.title: The One Where They're Going to Party
S4E9.des: The guys try to be spontaneous and wild. Rachel is offered a promotion. Monica must decide between a job as a head chef or her catering business.

S4E10.title: The One with the Girl from Poughkeepsie
S4E10.des: Ross struggles to maintain a long-distance relationship. Chandler tries to get a date for Rachel. Monica plots to establish authority at her new job.

S4E11.title: The One with Phoebe's Uterus
S4E11.des: Phoebe's half-brother makes an astounding announcement: He has married his older girlfriend and wants Phoebe to be a surrogate mother for them.

S4E12.title: The One with the Embryos
S4E12.des: Phoebe undergoes an embryo transplant and becomes pregnant. A simple challenge escalates into a full-blown contest between the guys and the women.

S4E13.title: The One with Rachel's Crush
S4E13.des: Chandler has a hard time with Kathy's new role in a play, in which she pretends to have sex with a handsome man. Rachel is attracted to a customer.

S4E14.title: The One with Joey's Dirty Day
S4E14.des: Joey has no time to shower after he comes home from a three-day fishing trip and has to head out to the set of Charlton Heston's new movie.

S4E15.title: The One with All the Rugby
S4E15.des: Chandler runs into Janice, now divorced, and finds her more irritating than ever. Ross plays rugby to impress Emily.

S4E16.title: The One with the Fake Party
S4E16.des: Rachel throws Emily a phony going-away party so she can see Joshua outside of work. Pregnant Phoebe craves meat.

S4E17.title: The One with the Free Porn
S4E17.des: The guys realize their TV is picking up a porno station for free. Phoebe discovers she's carrying triplets.

S4E18.title: The One with Rachel's New Dress
S4E18.des: Phoebe gets to name one of her babies. Rachel's plans to seduce her boyfriend go awry. Ross worries about his relationship with Emily.

S4E19.title: The One with All the Haste
S4E19.des: Monica and Rachel will do anything to get their old apartment back from the guys. Ross asks Emily to marry him.

S4E20.title: The One with the Wedding Dresses
S4E20.des: Monica wears Emily's wedding dress. Chandler forces Joey to get treatment for his snoring at a sleep clinic. Rachel proposes marriage to Joshua.

S4E21.title: The One with the Invitation
S4E21.des: Rachel and the engaged Ross reminisce separately about when they dated each other. The friends get invitations to Ross's wedding.

S4E22.title: The One with the Worst Best Man Ever
S4E22.des: After Joey almost loses Ross's wedding ring, Ross asks both Joey and Chandler to serve as his best man. The girls host a baby shower for Phoebe.

S4E23.title: The One with Ross's Wedding: Part 1
S4E23.des: In London for Ross's wedding, Chandler and Joey argue while sightseeing. After talking with Phoebe, Rachel realizes that she still loves Ross.

S4E24.title: The One with Ross's Wedding: Part 2
S4E24.des: Phoebe tries to warn the friends that Rachel is coming to London. Chandler and Monica develop a connection. Ross's father argues with Emily's father.

S7.about: Monica and Chandler prepare for their wedding but must deal with a competition between Rachel and Phoebe to be Monica's maid of honor.

S7E1.title: The One with Monica's Thunder
S7E1.des: Monica excitedly reveals the good news of her engagement to everyone -- but Rachel and Ross upstage her by reuniting.

S7E2.title: The One with Rachel's Book
S7E2.des: Joey finds out that Rachel is reading a steamy romance novel. Monica discovers that her parents have spent the money for her wedding on a beach house.

S7E3.title: The One with Phoebe's Cookies
S7E3.des: Monica becomes obsessed with acquiring Phoebe's secret, delicious cookie recipe. Joey accepts Rachel's help with sailing.

S7E4.title: The One with Rachel's Assistant
S7E4.des: Rachel wants to hire a cute, young male assistant over a more qualified woman. Joey's show gets cancelled.

S7E5.title: The One with the Engagement Picture
S7E5.des: Joey tries to teach Chandler how to smile for an engagement picture with Monica. Joey takes Tag out for a good time.

S7E6.title: The One with the Nap Partners
S7E6.des: Rachel and Phoebe compete to be Monica's maid of honor -- but Monica doesn't want to make the decision.

S7E7.title: The One with Ross' Library Book
S7E7.des: Ross discovers that his dissertation is in a section of the library where students go to have sex. Rachel and Phoebe meddle in Joey's relationship.

S7E8.title: The One Where Chandler Doesn't Like Dogs
S7E8.des: Chandler's irrational fear of dogs causes problems when Phoebe brings home a cute canine. Rachel's assistant gives her a Thanksgiving surprise.

S7E9.title: The One with All the Candy
S7E9.des: Monica becomes popular with her neighbors because of her homemade candy. Phoebe decides to learn to ride a bicycle.

S7E10.title: The One with the Holiday Armadillo
S7E10.des: Ross dresses up as the Holiday Armadillo and, with Monica, Chandler and Joey's help, teaches Ben about Chanukah.

S7E11.title: The One with All the Cheesecakes
S7E11.des: Chandler and Rachel can't help eating the irresistible cheesecakes intended for a neighbor. Phoebe's former boyfriend returns for one night only.

S7E12.title: The One Where They're Up All Night
S7E12.des: Monica falls asleep during sex. Rachel argues with Tag. Ross and Joey get stranded on the roof.

S7E13.title: The One Where Rosita Dies
S7E13.des: Phoebe becomes involved with a suicidal office worker. Rachel breaks Joey's favorite chair. Monica's beloved childhood belongings are destroyed.

S7E14.title: The One Where They All Turn Thirty
S7E14.des: Rachel's 30th birthday prompts the friends to reminisce about their own 30th birthdays.

S7E15.title: The One with Joey's New Brain
S7E15.des: Joey's character on a daytime drama becomes more prominent -- to the chagrin of the show's diva star.

S7E16.title: The One with the Truth About London
S7E16.des: Chandler finds out who Monica really wanted to have sex with on the night they became lovers. Ross is mad after Rachel teaches Ben practical jokes.

S7E17.title: The One with the Cheap Wedding Dress
S7E17.des: Monica battles another shopper for the perfect wedding dress. Ross and Joey compete for the same woman.

S7E18.title: The One with Joey's Award
S7E18.des: Joey overreacts at a daytime drama awards show. Ross deals with a male student who says he's in love with him.

S7E19.title: The One with Ross and Monica's Cousin
S7E19.des: Monica's gorgeous cousin unwittingly wreaks havoc on Chandler and Ross. Rachel and Phoebe hastily plan a surprise bridal party for Monica.

S7E20.title: The One with Rachel's Big Kiss
S7E20.des: Rachel reveals a titillating secret about her and a former sorority sister. Ross and Chandler compete for wedding tuxedos.

S7E21.title: The One with the Vows
S7E21.des: As Monica and Chandler prepare their wedding vows, everyone reminisces.

S7E22.title: The One with Chandler's Dad
S7E22.des: Chandler confronts his estranged, cross-dressing father. Rachel gets into trouble driving Monica's Porsche.

S7E23.title: The One with Chandler and Monica's Wedding: Part 1
S7E23.des: As the relatives gather for Monica and Chandler's wedding, Chandler finally realizes the magnitude of what he's doing.

S7E24.title: The One with Chandler and Monica's Wedding: Part 2
S7E24.des: Monica remains blissfully unaware of the potential disasters on her wedding day.

S5.about: The friends continue to haphazardly navigate their way through Manhattan, landing in more improbable situations than anyone has a right to imagine.

S5E1.title: The One After Ross Says Rachel
S5E1.des: Ross and Emily get married, but she cannot forgive him for calling her Rachel during the vows. Chandler and Monica search for a place to have sex.

S5E2.title: The One with All the Kissing
S5E2.des: Chandler kisses both Rachel and Phoebe in order to cover up a kiss he gave to Monica. Rachel finally tells Ross her feelings.

S5E3.title: The One Hundredth
S5E3.des: Phoebe goes into labor and is stuck with a doctor who is obsessed with the show "Happy Days." Monica plans a date with a male nurse to spite Chandler.

S5E4.title: The One Where Phoebe Hates PBS
S5E4.des: The gang discovers that Phoebe hates PBS. Emily tells Ross she'll give him a second chance only if he cuts all ties with Rachel.

S5E5.title: The One with the Kips
S5E5.des: Chandler and Monica plan a trip to Atlantic City for some private time. When Joey discovers that they are dating, they swear him to secrecy.

S5E6.title: The One with the Yeti
S5E6.des: Monica and Rachel are afraid of a hairy new neighbor -- until they find out how handsome he is with his hair cut.

S5E7.title: The One Where Ross Moves In
S5E7.des: After getting kicked out of his apartment, Ross moves in temporarily with Chandler and Joey, driving all three of them crazy.

S5E8.title: The One with All the Thanksgivings
S5E8.des: It's Thanksgiving, and the gang remembers former terrible Thanksgiving experiences. Chandler tells Monica that he loves her.

S5E9.title: The One with Ross's Sandwich
S5E9.des: Ross becomes upset when someone at work takes his sandwich from the refrigerator and eats it. Joey tries to cover for Chandler and Monica's dating.

S5E10.title: The One with the Inappropriate Sister
S5E10.des: Phoebe collects money for the Salvation Army during the holidays. Rachel is disturbed by her date's inappropriate relationship with his sister.

S5E11.title: The One with All the Resolutions
S5E11.des: The friends all make New Year's resolutions, but it looks like Rachel's resolution -- to stop gossiping -- is going to be the hardest to keep.

S5E12.title: The One with Chandler's Work Laugh
S5E12.des: Ross dates Janice after discovering that Emily is getting remarried. Monica hates the fake laugh that Chandler uses in response to his boss's jokes.

S5E13.title: The One with Joey's Bag
S5E13.des: Phoebe meets her father at her grandmother's funeral. Chandler discovers that Monica gives bad massages. Rachel dresses Joey for an audition.

S5E14.title: The One Where Everybody Finds Out
S5E14.des: Ross rents an apartment with a window facing Monica and Rachel's place. Phoebe sees Monica and Chandler having sex and learns the truth.

S5E15.title: The One with the Girl Who Hits Joey
S5E15.des: Joey's girlfriend likes to punch him. Ross alienates his new neighbors when he refuses to contribute to the retirement donation for the janitor.

S5E16.title: The One with the Cop
S5E16.des: After Phoebe finds a police badge, she uses it to do good deeds. Joey worries that he is in love with Monica.

S5E17.title: The One with Rachel's Inadvertent Kiss
S5E17.des: Rachel accidentally kisses the man interviewing her for a job. Joey becomes obsessed with a woman living in Ross' apartment complex.

S5E18.title: The One Where Rachel Smokes
S5E18.des: Rachel starts smoking when she realizes that her boss and co-workers at her new job are smokers. Joey and Ben audition for a commercial.

S5E19.title: The One Where Ross Can't Flirt
S5E19.des: Ross tries to flirt with the pizza delivery girl, with horrible results. Rachel loses a pair of earrings that Monica had lent to Phoebe.

S5E20.title: The One with the Ride-Along
S5E20.des: While the men are out, Emily leaves a message for Ross. Rachel, who was in Ross's apartment at the time, hears the message and accidentally erases it.

S5E21.title: The One with the Ball
S5E21.des: Gary asks Phoebe to move in with him. Monica and Chandler join Ross and Joey in a game of catch that lasts for hours.

S5E22.title: The One with Joey's Big Break
S5E22.des: Joey and Chandler take a road trip to Las Vegas, where Joey has landed the lead role in a movie. But the two argue and Joey goes on alone.

S5E23.title: The One in Vegas: Part 1
S5E23.des: The gang decides to go out to Las Vegas to surprise Joey and to celebrate Monica's and Chandler's one-year anniversary.

S5E24.title: The One in Vegas: Part 2
S5E24.des: Monica and Chandler reconcile and, on the roll of the dice, decide to go to a chapel and get married immediately.

S3.about: The shenanigans of the tightest circle of friends -- including Chandler and Joey adopting a duck -- continue as Season 3 plays out.

S3E1.title: The One with the Princess Leia Fantasy
S3E1.des: Ross reveals a fantasy to Rachel involving a certain Star Wars character.

S3E2.title: The One Where No One's Ready
S3E2.des: In a race against the clock, Ross tries to get the gang dressed and ready for a black-tie benefit at the museum.

S3E3.title: The One with the Jam
S3E3.des: After breaking up with Richard, Monica uses her free time to make jam and consider insemination via a sperm bank.

S3E4.title: The One with the Metaphorical Tunnel
S3E4.des: Ross panics when he sees his son with a Barbie doll. Phoebe poses as Joey's agent and gets him some good parts.

S3E5.title: The One with Frank Jr
S3E5.des: Phoebe's half-brother visits, and they have trouble bonding.

S3E6.title: The One with the Flashback
S3E6.des: When Janice asks the gang if any of them have ever slept together, the friends flash back to a time three years earlier.

S3E7.title: The One with the Race Car Bed
S3E7.des: Monica buys a new bed from Janice's soon-to-be-ex-husband, but the wrong one is delivered.

S3E8.title: The One with the Giant Poking Device
S3E8.des: Joey and Monica catch Janice kissing her ex-husband.

S3E9.title: The One with the Football
S3E9.des: The gang plays a game of touch football on Thanksgiving.

S3E10.title: The One Where Rachel Quits
S3E10.des: Rachel quits her job after Gunther tells her she needs to be retrained.

S3E11.title: The One Where Chandler Can't Remember Which Sister
S3E11.des: A drunken Chandler fools around with one of Joey's sisters -- but he can't remember which one.

S3E12.title: The One with All the Jealousy
S3E12.des: Ross becomes jealous when he thinks he catches Rachel's new co-worker flirting with her.

S3E13.title: The One Where Monica & Richard Are Just Friends
S3E13.des: Monica's willpower is tested when she runs into Richard at a video store.

S3E14.title: The One with Phoebe's Ex-Partner
S3E14.des: Phoebe is reunited with her former singing partner. Rachel's new job is putting a strain on her relationship with Ross.

S3E15.title: The One Where Ross & Rachel Take a Break
S3E15.des: Ross seeks solace at a party after a bitter fight with Rachel and ends up in the arms of another woman.

S3E16.title: The One The Morning After
S3E16.des: When Rachel discovers that Ross slept with Chloe, she decides to break up with him.

S3E17.title: The One Without the Ski Trip
S3E17.des: A lonely Ross visits Carol when Rachel goes on a ski trip with some friends.

S3E18.title: The One with the Hypnosis Tape
S3E18.des: Phoebe is distraught when her brother wants to marry a woman twice his age. A hypnosis tape makes Chandler act like a woman.

S3E19.title: The One with the Tiny T-Shirt
S3E19.des: Rachel goes on her first date since her breakup with Ross. Monica dates Pete, even though she is still not attracted to him.

S3E20.title: The One with the Dollhouse
S3E20.des: Joey thinks he's found his true love. Rachel's boss dates Chandler, creating big trouble for Rachel. Monica inherits a dollhouse.

S3E21.title: The One with a Chick. And a Duck
S3E21.des: When Pete buys a restaurant, Monica must decide whether to accept his offer of employment there. Joey and Chandler adopt a duck and a chick.

S3E22.title: The One with the Screamer
S3E22.des: Ross thinks that Rachel's date is crazy. Joey falls in love with Kate, but when she's offered a job in Los Angeles, she takes it.

S3E23.title: The One with Ross's Thing
S3E23.des: Ross finds a strange growth on his buttocks. Phoebe can't choose between two guys. Monica's boyfriend surprises her by not proposing marriage.

S3E24.title: The One with the Ultimate Fighting Champion
S3E24.des: To Monica's horror, Pete plans to be in an ultimate fight. Phoebe sets Ross up on a date with a woman who used to be bald.

S3E25.title: The One at the Beach
S3E25.des: The gang goes to the beach. Phoebe meets a family friend with links to her family's past. Ross discovers that Rachel still loves him.

S2.about: Rachel gets jealous of Ross's new girlfriend, Monica dates an older man, and Joey stars on a soap opera as the hit sitcom hits its stride in Season 2.

S2E1.title: The One with Ross's New Girlfriend
S2E1.des: Rachel waits at the airport for Ross, not knowing he is returning from China with his new girlfriend, Julie. Phoebe gives Monica an awful haircut.

S2E2.title: The One with the Breast Milk
S2E2.des: The guys are uncomfortable with the thought of Carol's breast milk, while Rachel is upset by Monica's growing friendship with Julie.

S2E3.title: The One Where Heckles Dies
S2E3.des: After Mr. Heckles dies and leaves all his belongings to Monica and Rachel, Chandler discovers he has eerie similarities with the late eccentric man.

S2E4.title: The One with Phoebe's Husband
S2E4.des: Phoebe has married a gay Canadian ice dancer to help him get his green card.

S2E5.title: The One with Five Steaks and an Eggplant
S2E5.des: Income issues divide the friends. Monica, Ross and Chandler have money; Phoebe, Rachel and Joey don't.

S2E6.title: The One with the Baby on the Bus
S2E6.des: Chandler and Joey lose Ross's son while checking out women on a bus.

S2E7.title: The One Where Ross Finds Out
S2E7.des: A drunken Rachel calls Ross and reveals her feelings for him on his answering machine. Now, Ross must make a decision between her and Julie.

S2E8.title: The One with the List
S2E8.des: Joey and Chandler try to help Ross with his decision to date Julie or Rachel by making a list of the pros and cons of each.

S2E9.title: The One with Phoebe's Dad
S2E9.des: In this Christmas episode, Phoebe tries to track down her real father.

S2E10.title: The One with Russ
S2E10.des: Rachel is dating a guy named Russ, and is blind to his uncanny resemblance to Ross.

S2E11.title: The One with the Lesbian Wedding
S2E11.des: Monica caters the wedding of Ross's ex-wife and her lesbian lover. Rachel learns that her mom and dad are getting a divorce.

S2E12.title: The One After the Super Bowl: Part 1
S2E12.des: Ross travels to San Diego to visit Marcel, his monkey. Joey is stalked by a fan of his daytime drama. First of a two-part episode.

S2E13.title: The One After the Super Bowl: Part 2
S2E13.des: Rachel and Monica compete for the affections of Jean-Claude Van Damme. Ross and Marcel go on a tour of the city. Second of a two-part episode.

S2E14.title: The One with the Prom Video
S2E14.des: Monica and Rachel's prom video reveals Monica's former girth, Rachel's former nose and the way Ross has always felt about Rachel.

S2E15.title: The One Where Ross and Rachel...You Know
S2E15.des: Ross and Rachel finally sleep together. Monica becomes infatuated with one of her parents' friends, for whom she caters a party.

S2E16.title: The One Where Joey Moves Out
S2E16.des: After having a fight with Chandler, Joey moves out. Monica's father finds out that Monica is dating his best friend.

S2E17.title: The One Where Eddie Moves In
S2E17.des: Joey considers moving back in with Chandler, but Chandler has a new roommate.

S2E18.title: The One Where Dr. Ramoray Dies
S2E18.des: Joey's soap opera character gets dropped down an elevator shaft after Joey brags about writing his own lines.

S2E19.title: The One Where Eddie Won't Go
S2E19.des: Chandler demands that his bizarre new roommate, Eddie, move out ... but Eddie won't go.

S2E20.title: The One Where Old Yeller Dies
S2E20.des: Phoebe's world view is shattered when she learns how "Old Yeller" really ends.

S2E21.title: The One with the Bullies
S2E21.des: Two bullies eject Chandler and Ross from Central Perk. Phoebe meets a brother she never knew she had.

S2E22.title: The One with the Two Parties
S2E22.des: Complications ensue when Rachel's estranged parents show up at the surprise party that the gang planned for her.

S2E23.title: The One with the Chicken Pox
S2E23.des: Phoebe catches chicken pox from the baby, just as her ex-boyfriend returns on shore leave from the Navy.

S2E24.title: The One with Barry and Mindy's Wedding
S2E24.des: Rachel agrees to be the maid of honor at her ex-fiancé's wedding.
